# FasloFasal Claim Verification Automation
#
# WHAT THIS APPLICATION DOES:
# This tool automates the repetitive process of verifying and approving agricultural insurance claims
# on the government portal fasalrin.gov.in. It handles the "REVIEW → Approve → Confirm → OK" workflow
# for each claim record, significantly reducing manual effort.
#
# KEY FEATURES:
# - Dry Run mode: Test the automation without making actual changes (safe for first-time use)
# - Live mode: Actually processes and approves claims (use after verifying Dry Run works correctly)
# - Configurable settings: Adjust timing, batch sizes, and timeouts as needed
# - Detailed logging: Records all actions for audit and troubleshooting
#
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE:
# This file contains the exact commands needed to launch the application.
#
# STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Open a terminal/command prompt in this project folder
# 2. Run the commands below in sequence
#
# TO LAUNCH THE APPLICATION:
cd /c/Projects/faslofasal/FasloFasal
/c/Projects/faslofasal/.venv/Scripts/python.exe gui.py
#
# AFTER LAUNCHING:
# - A graphical user interface will appear
# - Review the "Guide" tab for detailed usage instructions
# - Start with "Dry Run" enabled (recommended for first use)
# - Configure settings as needed in the "Settings" tab
# - Press "Start" to begin the automation process
#
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
# - Always verify Dry Run works correctly before switching to Live mode
# - The application requires manual login to the government portal on first run
# - Browser profiles are saved to avoid repeated logins
# - Check the "Log" tab during operation to monitor progress